    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for libpng.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The libpng packages contain a library of functions for creating and manipulating Portable Network Graphics (PNG) image format files.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libpng: libpng: Arbitrary code execution due to use-after-free vulnerability (CVE-2026-33416)\n\n* libpng: libpng: Information disclosure and denial of service via out-of-bounds read/write in Neon palette expansion (CVE-2026-33636)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      },
      {
